name: 3-pentanol, 3-methyl-, carbamate
Reason: 3-pentanol, 3-methyl-, carbamate has a melting point that we will compare to benzene, which has a melting point of 5.5 °C. The basic unit for our comparison is benzene, which has a melting point of 5.5 °C. The structural modifications we need to consider are the presence of a methyl group and a carbamate group. The methyl group adds approximately +5 °C due to increased molecular weight and rigidity. The carbamate group, on the other hand, can raise the melting point by approximately +10 °C due to the formation of hydrogen bonds and the increase in molecular weight.
